<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/255: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-15T17:00:00-03:00">July 15,
                                    1932—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 15—4:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>66. Following telegram has been received from the Consul at Porto Alegre:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“July 15, 10 a.m. Everything quiet. Interventor controls
                                    situation. Northerly movement of troops has continued.</p>
                                <p>Archbishop has begun conferring with Interventor and the United
                                    Front leaders in order to attempt initiation of church movement
                                    for peace at São Paulo. Official report states that he was well
                                    received by all which is credible. Emissary Liberator Party has
                                    been sent to Buenos Aires at the request of <persName corresp="#p_ABJFd1">Assis</persName>, Brazil Supreme Chief
                                    of the party, to acquaint him with the situation, a circumstance
                                    involving further delay to politicians”.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>